The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Stoner wins
                                                                                                                                                                                                     Stoner wins
                      
	Melbourne: Australias Casey Stoner overcame a persistent wrist injury to win his home MotoGP at Phillip Island for the second successive year on Sunday.         
	Stoner, who is to have surgery to fix a broken bone in his wrist at the end of the season, led from start to finish on his Ducati to beat world champion Valentino Rossi and American Nicky Hayden. (Reuters)                                                                                                                          
